OL,3,CCoroner urges government to act after
OL,4,Cman drowns at open water swimming event
OL,6,FA coroner has urged the government to
OL,7,Ftake action after a 55-year-old man
OL,8,Fdrowned at an open water swimming
OL,9,Fevent.
OL,11,FJoel Kenneth Ineson died at Hetton
OL,12,FLyons Park, in Sunderland, on 1 June
OL,13,F2023 after suffering a cardiac event
OL,14,Fwhile taking part in an organised open
OL,15,Fwater swim.
OL,17,FAt the conclusion of an inquest held
OL,18,Fon 4 April, David Place, senior
OL,19,Fcoroner for the City of Sunderland,
OL,20,Frecorded a conclusion of accidental
OL,21,Fdeath.
