OL,4,Cman drowns at open water swimming event
OL,6,FThe medical cause of death was given
OL,7,Fas drowning, with diffuse myocardial
OL,8,Fscarring as a contributing factor.
OL,10,FIn a formal report aimed at preventing
OL,11,Ffuture deaths, Mr Place warned that
OL,12,Fthe growing popularity of open water
OL,13,Fswimming was not matched by sufficient
OL,14,Foversight or regulation.
OL,16,FHe said Mr Ineson had a "reasonable
OL,17,Fexpectation that appropriate safety
OL,18,Fmeasures would be in place" at the
OL,19,Fevent, which was organised, well
OL,20,Fattended and charged participants a
OL,21,Fsmall fee.
